<p>A fast-moving blaze tore through the Saganoseki area of Oita on Kyushu on the evening of Tuesday, November 18, destroying or damaging about 170 buildings and forcing mass evacuations as firefighters battled the flames into Wednesday morning. Local media and authorities reported at least one person killed and another person reported missing as emergency crews searched damaged neighbourhoods. Officials and crews mounted aerial firefighting operations, deploying helicopters as the flames spread quickly through hilly residential areas overlooking a coastal fishing harbour.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/UVs5N2VSBD7DzthwJ8BfjAreEz1b9C3MnLZw-8rHVX_ZJwB-iwWfWt6L6siXZsDsQA4H8ZHtsRA62ZL3pvhf2F8yVFaBdPyHH67fyMzjgKkBT1xHDt9hT4fNY3EtCSzWZpvFtlXK98gcjQnKTUGlMLf1E4U5NTQ0h2NHRbDA0Q' alt='Smoke and flames rising over a residential area in Oita after the fire swept through neighbourhoods' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Historical scale: Japanese and regional outlets described the blaze as the largest urban fire in the country in nearly 50 years, underlining its extraordinary scale for a modern city.</li><li>Local economy: The affected Saganoseki district overlooks a fishing harbour famed for Seki-brand mackerel, raising concerns about damage near coastal fisheries and processing areas.</li><li>Visual evidence: Aerial footage released by broadcasters showed houses reduced to rubble and thick smoke plumes, imagery that helped authorities assess damage from above.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Oita city authorities: Officials reported mass evacuations and said emergency crews were searching damaged neighbourhoods while firefighting operations continued. (<a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/fire-burning-southwestern-japan-damages-170-homes-forces-127653292'>ABC News</a>)</li><li>Regional broadcasters and media: Local broadcasters released aerial footage showing widespread destruction and thick plumes of smoke over the Saganoseki district. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/east-asia/article/3333399/japans-worst-urban-fire-48-years-kills-1-destroys-170-buildings'>SCMP</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/fire-burning-southwestern-japan-damages-170-homes-forces-127653292'>Fire burning in southwestern Japan damages 170 homes, forces evacuations</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='http://www.euronews.com/video/2025/11/19/fire-in-japan-burns-170-homes-and-forces-mass-evacuations'>Fire in Japan burns 170 homes and forces mass evacuations</a> - euronews.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/fire-in-southwestern-japan-damages-170-homes-forces-evacuations-one-missing/article70297372.ece'>Japan’s biggest fire in nearly 50 years ravages 170 buildings, kills one</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/japan-fire-forces-170-buildings-to-evacuate-one-missing/a-74798967'>Japan: Fire forces 170 buildings to evacuate, one missing</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/east-asia/article/3333399/japans-worst-urban-fire-48-years-kills-1-destroys-170-buildings'>Japan’s largest urban fire in decades devastates 170 buildings</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/videos/cx207dw3v5yo'>Japan&#x27;s largest urban fire in decades rips through 170 buildings</a> - bbc.com</li></ul>